         The thing that made CoS overpowering in PVP was the instacast the items you listed are not insta cast.  Sure lots have see invis items but this doesnt mean everyone has one.  With the CoS you could cast, invis, move, repeat and people could never catch you.  If someone was casting a spell on you and didnt have see invis just click the CoS and they loose their target.  </P><P>Look back at when they changed the CoS you will notice it is around the same time that they changed invis to cause you to loose your target.  Verant even stated that is why they changed it.  </P><P>Reguardless this is an off topic.  I think the real issue is the vast majority of EQ players are on blue servers thus the game is going to be balanced for blue servers before red servers.  It would be foolish to do it the other way around.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
